Caldera became a radio artist in 1968 and recorded his first hit song Thara Petia in 1972.
He subsequently released a four song album in 1977.
In 1979, the Prime Minister of Sri Lanka, Ranasinghe Premadasa, donated a house for Caldera to live.
In 1993, Caldera received a Kala Bhushana award (the second highest award granted by the state to performing artists).
He was diagnosed with cancer in 2004 and died on 11 October 2006.
